# Updating LLMRouter Documentation Website

## 1. Update Content

Edit markdown files in the `docs/` directory:

```bash
# Edit via command line
vim docs/index.md

vim docs/[target_file].md
# etc.
```

Or you may edit using the IDE.

## 2. Deploy to GitHub Pages

```bash
# From project root
mkdocs gh-deploy
```

Your updated site will be live at: `https://ulab-uiuc.github.io/LLMRouter/`. This process may take 10~20 seconds.

## 3. Update RunLLM

RunLLM automatically syncs with your deployed documentation. To trigger an update:

1. **Wait one week** (automatic sync), OR
2. **Manual sync** via RunLLM dashboard:
   - Go to [RunLLM Dashboard](https://runllm.com)
   - Navigate to your project settings
   - Click "Sync Documentation"

